tool_description: Programmatic access to Chrome extension stats and download Chrome extensions.
title: Chrome-Stats

api_list.name: Raw data - Download
api_list.description:
Download the specified raw data CSV. The `key` is the raw data CSV file name provided by the Raw data - List API.
Note that this endpoint will redirect to a S3 URL for download, and should not be used within the browser due to CORS restriction.

api_list.name: Search (Advanced)
api_list.description: Run an advanced search query for extensions or reviews
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://chrome-stats.p.rapidapi.com/api/advanced-search"

headers = {
    "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
    "X-RapidAPI-Host": "chrome-stats.p.rapidapi.com"
}

response = requests.post(url, headers=headers)

print(response.json())

api_list.name: Ranking - Extensions
api_list.description:
Return a list of extensions, sorted by their ranking in the given namespace.

A namespace can be the overall-rank, or the type of item in Chrome Web Store (extension, app, or theme), or a category.

required_parameters.name: namespace
required_parameters.description: Should be one of the namespaces in /api/metastats
